summary: Cristiano Ronaldo continues to dominate the world of football as he reaches remarkable milestones. With his 900th career goal against Croatia in the UEFA Nations League, he becomes the first player to achieve this extraordinary feat. His goal against Scotland in a 2-1 victory solidified his position as Europe's most-capped men's international player with 214 appearances for Portugal. Ronaldo's impressive statistics reveal his dominance across six teams, including countless records and iconic strikes. Despite Scott McTominay's heroics for Scotland, Ronaldo's late goal shattered their hopes of victory. The legendary striker's milestone moments have cemented his place in football history, sparking comparisons to his rival Lionel Messi in the ongoing debate over who has scored the most goals.

name: Kathy Bates
summary: Veteran actress Kathy Bates has announced her retirement from acting after completing her role in the upcoming "Matlock" reboot on CBS. Bates, known for her award-winning performances in films and television shows such as "Misery" and "The Office," cited the demanding nature of her craft as one of the reasons for her decision. She described her time on the "Matlock" reboot as her "last dance" and expressed gratitude for the opportunity to revisit the iconic character. Bates expressed her desire to spend more time pursuing other interests, including writing, and to focus on her personal life. This retirement marks the end of a remarkable career that has spanned several decades and has brought Bates numerous accolades, including an Academy Award, two Golden Globe Awards, and two Emmy Awards.
